  30 Sep 2010; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org> adhearsion-0.8.3-r1.ebuild:
  Marking adhearsion-0.8.3-r1 ~ppc64 for bug 306909

*adhearsion-0.8.6 (18 Sep 2010)

  18 Sep 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +adhearsion-0.8.6.ebuild:
  Version bump.

  30 Aug 2010; Mark Loeser <halcy0n@gentoo.org> adhearsion-0.8.3.ebuild:
  Drop ppc64 due to dependency dev-ruby/rubigen not being keyworded

*adhearsion-0.8.4 (28 Jun 2010)

  28 Jun 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +adhearsion-0.8.4.ebuild:
  Version bump.

  12 Jun 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -adhearsion-0.8.2.ebuild:
  Remove old version.

*adhearsion-0.8.3-r1 (12 Jun 2010)

  12 Jun 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  +adhearsion-0.8.3-r1.ebuild:
  Move to ruby-fakegem, but without the ppc64 keyword due to bug 306909.

  12 Jun 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> adhearsion-0.8.3.ebuild:
  Move ppc64 keyword forward since that seems to have been the intention.

  06 Jan 2010; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org> adhearsion-0.8.2.ebuild:
  Marking adhearsion-0.8.2 ~ppc64 for bug 276701

*adhearsion-0.8.3 (09 Dec 2009)

  09 Dec 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +adhearsion-0.8.3.ebuild:
  Version bump with bug fixes.

  22 Aug 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -adhearsion-0.7.7.ebuild:
  Remove old version.

  08 Jul 2009; Christian Faulhammer <fauli@gentoo.org>
  adhearsion-0.8.2.ebuild:
  keyworded ~arch for x86, bug 276701

*adhearsion-0.8.2 (06 Jul 2009)

  06 Jul 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +adhearsion-0.8.2.ebuild:
  Version bump. Large rewrite with many changes.
  Dropped ~ppc64 and ~x86 dependency due to new dev-ruby/rubigen dependency,
  bug #276701.

  05 Jun 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -adhearsion-0.7.5.ebuild:
  Remove old version.

